		</fdd:documentation>
		<fdd:adoption>AVI is widely adopted for video production and filemaking; in 2000 or earlier, the expert commentator <a href="http://www.jmcgowan.com/avicodecs.html">John McGowan</a> wrote, "Indeo R3.2 is one of the default Video for Windows codecs."
